shared.definitions

Enum PlayerIndex

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<PlayerIndex>
      • shared.definitions.PlayerIndex
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<PlayerIndex>

    public enum PlayerIndex
extends java.lang.Enum<PlayerIndex>
    Defines the indexs that can be used for players.

    NONE is used to either specify that some object is coming from the server, or that no player is associated with it. There are only four player indexes (0-3).
